President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has announced the formation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the Inauguration of His Excellency Yoon Suk Yeol in Seoul, Republic of Korea on May 10, 2022. The delegation will be led by Mr. Douglas Emhoff, the Second Gentleman of the United States. Other members of the delegation include Mr. Christopher Del Corso, Chargé d’Affaires ad interim at the U.S. Embassy in Seoul, The Honorable Martin J. Walsh, Secretary of Labor of the United States, The Honorable Ami Bera, United States Representative (D) from California, The Honorable Marilyn Strickland, United States Representative (D) from Washington, The Honorable Todd Sunhwae Kim, Assistant Attorney General at the Department of Justice, The Honorable Linda Hee Jung Shim, Special Assistant to the President for Economic Agency Personnel, and Ms. Min Jin Lee, an Author and Writer-in-Residence at Amherst College.